Hey Cliff,

 I'm still wondering if you're still needed help with your German cockroach infestation.  

My protocol is an initial non-repellent liquid residual with gel baits & glue traps so that the roaches can bring the product back to where they're harboring in places we can't reach.  It's called the transfer effect and it will kill all the roaches that are in areas that we can't reach.  

If it's really bad some German cockroach infestations need a fumigation treatment.  That's why I need to inspect to see the severity of the infestation.

Then on the 7-10 day follow-up treatment, it's a total clean out, the roaches are pretty much gone!!  

The whole protocol is included at one price.  But I do have to do the inspection first to check out the severity of the infestation but I am very good at what I do.  

Feel free to read my reviews and go to my Facebook page.  You'll find the FB address page down at the bottom of my letter...  Just tap it and it will go to my Facebook page...

Sincerely

Tony Costa
Owner-Operator
Metro Pest Tech,LLC
